sidle
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to negotiable a steep slope of a hill by going round the side of it rather than straight up to the crest. (probably a back form from SIDELING.)
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
